Package cmpt355.project.codegen

Class CompileContext

java.lang.Object
cmpt355.project.codegen.CompileContext
public class CompileContext
extends Object
The main class used when generating JVM assembly code. Each CompileContext is specific to a single method and contains
  • a list of all the local variables (including parameters) in the method with their mapping to the local variable array;
  • the generated code of the method (a list of Instructions);
  • Labels for branch targets.
The main methods of use are
  • addCode(Instruction) — adds an instruction to the method's code;
  • findMethodVariable(String) — returns the index of a local variable (or parameter) in the method's local variable array;
  • newLabel(String) — creates a new label that can be used as a branch target.

    • findMethodVariable

      public int findMethodVariable​(String name)
      Returns the index of a local variable (or parameter) in the local variable array (as would be used by e.g. Instruction.new_istore(int).
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the local variable to look up
      Returns:
      an index (≥ 0, or ≥ 1 if in a non-static method)
      Throws:
      InternalCompilerException - if name is not the name of a local variable in this method

    • newLabel

      public Label newLabel​(String tag)
      Creates a new label with the given tag, which will be incorporated into the generated label in the assembly code for easier debugging. The tag must consist of letters, digits, and underscores. A tag must be mark()ed at the point of the code that it should branch to. See Label for more information.
      Parameters:
      tag - the tag, or null if no tag is desired.
      Returns:
      a Label that can be used as the target of branch instructions.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if tag contains any characters other than (ASCII) letters, digits, or underscores.
